<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<body>
<p>Hello {{ first_name }},</p>

<p>Your personal user account has been created to access the HPC cluster.</p>

<h3>I. Access to the login nodes</h3>

<p>The first step is to establish a VPN tunnel to the HPC infrastructure.</p>

<p>Your VPN credentials:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Username:</strong> {{ username }}</li>
{% if vpn_password %}
  <li><strong>VPN password:</strong> {{ vpn_password }}</li>
{% endif %}
</ul>

<p><strong>IMPORTANT:</strong> Please change your VPN password after the
first successful SSH login.</p>

<p>The second step is to log into the login node using your username
<code>{{ username }}</code> and the SSH key registered for you.</p>

<h3>II. Storage allocations</h3>

<p>Personal home folder: <code>{{ home_directory }}</code></p>

<p>Note that the home folder has limited capacity (~2 GiB).
Do not store anything large there.</p>

<h3>III. Slurm project account</h3>

<p>Use the assigned SLURM project account when submitting jobs.</p>

<p>Please let us know if you experience any issues accessing the cluster.</p>

<p>Best regards,<br>HPC Support Team</p>
</body>
</html>
